cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of grant-free random access with massive IoT devices, which involves issues related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and control systems (cs.SY). The proposed approach also involves machine learning techniques such as multi-armed bandit algorithms, which fall under the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the use of low-precision analog-to-digital converters (ADCs), which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves the processing of audio or sensor data.
